headline: Bitcoin Price Drops Below $90,000
summary: Bitcoin fell below $90,000 on Wednesday, with investors continuing to pull back from speculative and riskier corners of the market. The largest cryptocurrency has erased its year-to-date gains and now trades about 30% off its all-time high set on Oct.

headline: Investors pull record $523 million from BlackRock's flagship bitcoin ETF
summary: (Reuters) -Investors pulled roughly $523 million from BlackRock's flagship iShares Bitcoin Trust on Tuesday, according ​to data from Farside Investors, marking the fund's largest single-day withdrawal ‌since its launch.  IBIT, the largest spot bitcoin ETF, has attracted strong investor demand since its launch in January 2024 and has been central to the crypto ETF boom.  "The crypto market entered a hangover in August," said Kraken's ​Global Economist Thomas Perfumo, adding a lot of that demand was driven by borrowed ‌money.

headline: Bitcoin Slide Spurs Record Withdrawals From BlackRock’s IBIT
summary: BlackRock saw $523 million in outflows from the exchange-traded fund on Tuesday, marking a fifth straight day of net redemptions and its highest on record, according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  It has amassed more than $72 billion in assets with nearly $26 billion of inflows this year.
